      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KOORINGA ELLSIE (2) is a smart type who sailed across from an outside draw to score an all the way win (23.73) at this track in Maiden over 411m. Brilliant beginner who should be leading the way here. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. PRECIOUS WONDER (6) hit the ground running last start and was never headed to land her maiden success over 350m at Grafton (20.13). Expecting another bold showing. PRECIOUS GLOW (3) finished well back at Grafton last time when a 4.5 lengths sixth (20.40) but scored three back at Grafton (20.11). Some good form is emerging from her last run. One of the better hopes. TINY BUT MIGHTY (1) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can bounce back.",
